law.text: Any person who violates any provision of KRS 317B.010 to 317B.060 shall be fined not less than fifty dollars ($50) nor more than five hundred dollars ($500) or imprisoned for not less than ten (10) days nor more than six (6) months, or be subject to both the fine and the imprisonment.
law.history: Created 2003 Ky. Acts ch. 137, sec. 11, effective June 24, 2003.
